OL,3,C'We have a vibrant culture but it's
OL,4,Cvery rare to get spaces that welcome
OL,5,Cus'
OL,7,F"Unique throughout Europe, throughout
OL,8,Fthe world really.
OL,10,F"I come from a Romani family in Kent.
OL,11,FThe connections throughout all the
OL,12,Fdifferent groups around the UK,
OL,13,Fparticularly here in Wales actually
OL,14,Fare very strong."
OL,16,FHe added: "Wales is pioneering for
OL,17,FGypsy, Roma and Traveller culture in
OL,18,Freally emphasising funding for the
OL,19,Farts. This kind of thing is not
OL,20,Fhappening in other parts of the UK so
OL,21,FWales should be really proud of that."
